Note:
BITSET - Fixed-Width Bit Array Tier 0 Primitive

This file implements a bitset over int64 words. Bits are addressed
0..num_bits-1; bit i lives in words[i / 64] at position (i mod 64),
counting from the least-significant bit. The bitset stores num_bits
and num_words explicitly so it can be resized later without rebuilding.

Bitset structure (24 bytes):
  offset 0:  words pointer (8 bytes) - array of int64
  offset 8:  num_bits     (8 bytes) - logical bit count
  offset 16: num_words    (8 bytes) - ceil(num_bits / 64)

Use cases:
- Reachability marks in dataflow
- Free / used slot tracking for slab allocators
- Bloom-style filters where exact bit access is needed
- Compact integer set when the universe is small and dense

Set operations come in two forms:
  - "_into": destination receives the result, neither source modified
  - "_in_place": left operand modified, right operand read-only

All operations on two bitsets require the two operands to share the
same num_bits. The "_into" variants assert the destination shares the
same num_bits or returns 0 (no allocation).
:End Note

Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/memory/layout.runa" as Layout
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/memory_core.runa" as Memory

Note: ============================================================================
Note: CONSTANTS
Note: ============================================================================

Let BITSET_HEADER_SIZE be 24
Let BITSET_WORD_BITS be 64
Let BITSET_WORD_BYTES be 8
Let BITSET_FULL_WORD be -1
Let BITSET_NOT_FOUND be -1

Note: ============================================================================
Note: INTERNAL HELPERS
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Compute the number of int64 words needed to hold num_bits bits.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Returns (num_bits + 63) / 64. Handles num_bits == 0 by returning 0.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
num_bits must be non-negative.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "bitset_words_for_bits" takes num_bits as Integer returns Integer:
    If num_bits is less than or equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let total be num_bits plus 63
    Return total divided by BITSET_WORD_BITS
End Process

@Reasoning
Address of words[index] given the words pointer.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
words + index * 8.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Caller-validated index.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "bitset_word_addr" takes words as Integer, index as Integer returns Integer:
    Return words plus (index multiplied by BITSET_WORD_BYTES)
End Process

@Reasoning
Build a mask that has exactly the low (num_bits mod 64) bits set.
Used to clear trailing bits in the last word after bulk-fill or
complement operations so the bitset never reports bits outside its
logical range.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
1) rem = num_bits mod 64.
2) If rem == 0, return all-ones (the last word is fully in-range).
3) Otherwise return (1 << rem) - 1.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Pure function.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "bitset_tail_mask" takes num_bits as Integer returns Integer:
    Let rem be num_bits modulo by BITSET_WORD_BITS
    If rem is equal to 0:
        Return BITSET_FULL_WORD
    End If
    Let one be 1
    Let shifted be one shifted left by rem
    Return shifted minus 1
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: CONSTRUCTION / DESTRUCTION
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Allocate a new bitset of num_bits bits, all initialized to zero.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
1) Compute num_words via bitset_words_for_bits.
2) Allocate header (24 bytes).
3) Allocate num_words * 8 bytes for the word array.
4) Zero the word array.
5) Initialize header fields.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(num_words).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on allocation failure. num_bits <= 0 returns a degenerate
empty bitset with num_words = 0 and a null words pointer to avoid
empty-allocation oddities.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "bitset_create" takes num_bits as Integer returns Integer:
    Let bs be proc allocate from Layout with BITSET_HEADER_SIZE
    If bs is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with bs, 0, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with bs, 8, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with bs, 16, 0
    If num_bits is less than or equal to 0:
        Return bs
    End If
    Let num_words be proc bitset_words_for_bits with num_bits
    Let bytes be num_words multiplied by BITSET_WORD_BYTES
    Let words be proc allocate from Layout with bytes
    If words is equal to 0:
        proc deallocate from Layout with bs
        Return 0
    End If
    proc memory_fill from Memory with words, 0, bytes
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with bs, 0, words
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with bs, 8, num_bits
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with bs, 16, num_words
    Return bs
End Process

@Reasoning
Release the bitset and its word array.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Frees the word array (if non-null) then the header.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1) (allocator-bounded).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Caller-owned; do not pass the same pointer twice.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "bitset_destroy" takes bs as Integer returns Integer:
    If bs is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let words be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with bs, 0
    If words is not equal to 0:
        proc deallocate from Layout with words
    End If
    proc deallocate from Layout with bs
    Return 1
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: STATE QUERIES
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Total number of bits managed by the bitset.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Returns the num_bits field at offset 8.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Read-only.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "bitset_size" takes bs as Integer returns Integer:
    If bs is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with bs, 8
End Process

@Reasoning
Number of int64 words in the backing array.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Returns the num_words field at offset 16.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Read-only.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "bitset_word_count" takes bs as Integer returns Integer:
    If bs is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with bs, 16
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: BIT-LEVEL OPERATIONS
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Set the bit at position i to 1. No-op if i is out of range.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
1) Bounds check.
2) word_index = i / 64; bit_pos = i mod 64.
3) Load words[word_index], OR with (1 << bit_pos), store back.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Out-of-range i is ignored to support speculative callers (e.g.
iterators that might overshoot on the final word).
@End Security_Scope
Process called "bitset_set" takes bs as Integer, i as Integer returns Integer:
    If bs is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let num_bits be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with bs, 8
    If i is less than 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If i is greater than or equal to num_bits:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let words be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with bs, 0
    Let word_index be i divided by BITSET_WORD_BITS
    Let bit_pos be i modulo by BITSET_WORD_BITS
    Let one be 1
    Let mask be one shifted left by bit_pos
    Let addr be proc bitset_word_addr with words, word_index
    Let cur be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with addr, 0
    Let updated be cur bitwise or mask
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with addr, 0, updated
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning
Clear the bit at position i to 0.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
1) Bounds check.
2) Load words[i / 64], AND with NOT (1 << (i mod 64)).
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Out-of-range i is ignored.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "bitset_clear" takes bs as Integer, i as Integer returns Integer:
    If bs is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let num_bits be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with bs, 8
    If i is less than 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If i is greater than or equal to num_bits:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let words be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with bs, 0
    Let word_index be i divided by BITSET_WORD_BITS
    Let bit_pos be i modulo by BITSET_WORD_BITS
    Let one be 1
    Let bit_mask be one shifted left by bit_pos
    Let inv_mask be bit_mask bitwise xor BITSET_FULL_WORD
    Let addr be proc bitset_word_addr with words, word_index
    Let cur be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with addr, 0
    Let updated be cur bitwise and inv_mask
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with addr, 0, updated
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning
Toggle the bit at position i (0 -> 1, 1 -> 0).
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
1) Bounds check.
2) words[i/64] = words[i/64] XOR (1 << (i mod 64)).
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Out-of-range i is ignored.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "bitset_toggle" takes bs as Integer, i as Integer returns Integer:
    If bs is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let num_bits be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with bs, 8
    If i is less than 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If i is greater than or equal to num_bits:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let words be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with bs, 0
    Let word_index be i divided by BITSET_WORD_BITS
    Let bit_pos be i modulo by BITSET_WORD_BITS
    Let one be 1
    Let mask be one shifted left by bit_pos
    Let addr be proc bitset_word_addr with words, word_index
    Let cur be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with addr, 0
    Let updated be cur bitwise xor mask
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with addr, 0, updated
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning
Test the bit at position i. Returns 1 if set, 0 if clear.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
1) Bounds check.
2) Load words[i / 64], shift right by (i mod 64), mask with 1.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Out-of-range i returns 0.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "bitset_test" takes bs as Integer, i as Integer returns Integer:
    If bs is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let num_bits be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with bs, 8
    If i is less than 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If i is greater than or equal to num_bits:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let words be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with bs, 0
    Let word_index be i divided by BITSET_WORD_BITS
    Let bit_pos be i modulo by BITSET_WORD_BITS
    Let addr be proc bitset_word_addr with words, word_index
    Let cur be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with addr, 0
    Let bit_val be (cur shifted right by bit_pos) bitwise and 1
    Return bit_val
End Process

@Reasoning
Set all bits to 0. Maintains num_bits and num_words; only zeros words.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
memory_fill the word array with zeros.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(num_words).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Read-only on header.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "bitset_clear_all" takes bs as Integer returns Integer:
    If bs is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let words be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with bs, 0
    Let num_words be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with bs, 16
    If words is equal to 0:
        Return 1
    End If
    If num_words is equal to 0:
        Return 1
    End If
    Let bytes be num_words multiplied by BITSET_WORD_BYTES
    proc memory_fill from Memory with words, 0, bytes
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning
Set all logical bits to 1. The trailing partial word, if any, is
masked so out-of-range bits remain zero. This guarantees popcount,
find_first_clear, and complement give consistent results.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
1) Fill all words with -1.
2) If num_bits is not a multiple of 64, mask the last word with the
   tail mask so bits beyond num_bits stay 0.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(num_words).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Read-only on header.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "bitset_set_all" takes bs as Integer returns Integer:
    If bs is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let num_bits be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with bs, 8
    Let num_words be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with bs, 16
    Let words be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with bs, 0
    If num_words is equal to 0:
        Return 1
    End If
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than num_words:
        Let addr be proc bitset_word_addr with words, i
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with addr, 0, BITSET_FULL_WORD
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    Let rem be num_bits modulo by BITSET_WORD_BITS
    If rem is not equal to 0:
        Let mask be proc bitset_tail_mask with num_bits
        Let last_addr be proc bitset_word_addr with words, num_words minus 1
        Let cur be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with last_addr, 0
        Let trimmed be cur bitwise and mask
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with last_addr, 0, trimmed
    End If
    Return 1
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: SET OPERATIONS - IN-PLACE
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Compute lhs := lhs OR rhs in place. Both bitsets must agree on
num_bits; otherwise nothing is done and 0 is returned.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Word-wise OR over min(num_words_lhs, num_words_rhs).
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(num_words).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 if num_bits mismatch.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "bitset_union_in_place" takes lhs as Integer, rhs as Integer returns Integer:
    If lhs is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If rhs is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let n_l be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with lhs, 8
    Let n_r be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with rhs, 8
    If n_l is not equal to n_r:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let nw be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with lhs, 16
    Let w_l be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with lhs, 0
    Let w_r be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with rhs, 0
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than nw:
        Let a_l be proc bitset_word_addr with w_l, i
        Let a_r be proc bitset_word_addr with w_r, i
        Let v_l be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with a_l, 0
        Let v_r be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with a_r, 0
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with a_l, 0, v_l bitwise or v_r
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning
lhs := lhs AND rhs in place.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Word-wise AND.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(num_words).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on num_bits mismatch.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "bitset_intersection_in_place" takes lhs as Integer, rhs as Integer returns Integer:
    If lhs is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If rhs is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let n_l be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with lhs, 8
    Let n_r be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with rhs, 8
    If n_l is not equal to n_r:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let nw be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with lhs, 16
    Let w_l be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with lhs, 0
    Let w_r be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with rhs, 0
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than nw:
        Let a_l be proc bitset_word_addr with w_l, i
        Let a_r be proc bitset_word_addr with w_r, i
        Let v_l be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with a_l, 0
        Let v_r be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with a_r, 0
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with a_l, 0, v_l bitwise and v_r
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning
lhs := lhs AND NOT rhs in place (set difference).
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Word-wise (lhs AND (NOT rhs)).
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(num_words).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on num_bits mismatch.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "bitset_difference_in_place" takes lhs as Integer, rhs as Integer returns Integer:
    If lhs is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If rhs is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let n_l be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with lhs, 8
    Let n_r be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with rhs, 8
    If n_l is not equal to n_r:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let nw be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with lhs, 16
    Let w_l be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with lhs, 0
    Let w_r be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with rhs, 0
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than nw:
        Let a_l be proc bitset_word_addr with w_l, i
        Let a_r be proc bitset_word_addr with w_r, i
        Let v_l be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with a_l, 0
        Let v_r be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with a_r, 0
        Let not_r be v_r bitwise xor BITSET_FULL_WORD
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with a_l, 0, v_l bitwise and not_r
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning
lhs := lhs XOR rhs in place (symmetric difference).
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Word-wise XOR.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(num_words).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on num_bits mismatch.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "bitset_xor_in_place" takes lhs as Integer, rhs as Integer returns Integer:
    If lhs is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If rhs is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let n_l be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with lhs, 8
    Let n_r be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with rhs, 8
    If n_l is not equal to n_r:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let nw be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with lhs, 16
    Let w_l be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with lhs, 0
    Let w_r be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with rhs, 0
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than nw:
        Let a_l be proc bitset_word_addr with w_l, i
        Let a_r be proc bitset_word_addr with w_r, i
        Let v_l be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with a_l, 0
        Let v_r be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with a_r, 0
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with a_l, 0, v_l bitwise xor v_r
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    Let num_bits be n_l
    Let rem be num_bits modulo by BITSET_WORD_BITS
    If rem is not equal to 0:
        Let mask be proc bitset_tail_mask with num_bits
        Let last_addr be proc bitset_word_addr with w_l, nw minus 1
        Let cur be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with last_addr, 0
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with last_addr, 0, cur bitwise and mask
    End If
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning
lhs := NOT lhs (complement). Bits beyond num_bits are kept zero.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
1) Word-wise XOR with -1.
2) Mask the last word with tail_mask if num_bits is not a multiple of 64.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(num_words).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Caller-owned.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "bitset_complement_in_place" takes bs as Integer returns Integer:
    If bs is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let num_bits be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with bs, 8
    Let nw be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with bs, 16
    Let words be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with bs, 0
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than nw:
        Let addr be proc bitset_word_addr with words, i
        Let cur be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with addr, 0
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with addr, 0, cur bitwise xor BITSET_FULL_WORD
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    Let rem be num_bits modulo by BITSET_WORD_BITS
    If rem is not equal to 0:
        Let mask be proc bitset_tail_mask with num_bits
        Let last_addr be proc bitset_word_addr with words, nw minus 1
        Let cur_last be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with last_addr, 0
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with last_addr, 0, cur_last bitwise and mask
    End If
    Return 1
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: SET OPERATIONS - NEW-RESULT (allocate fresh destination)
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Allocate a new bitset that holds the bitwise union of lhs and rhs.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
1) num_bits mismatch -> return 0.
2) Allocate fresh bitset of the same num_bits.
3) Word-wise OR into the new bitset.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(num_words). Allocates a new bitset.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on num_bits mismatch or allocation failure.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "bitset_union" takes lhs as Integer, rhs as Integer returns Integer:
    If lhs is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If rhs is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let n_l be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with lhs, 8
    Let n_r be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with rhs, 8
    If n_l is not equal to n_r:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let result be proc bitset_create with n_l
    If result is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let nw be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with lhs, 16
    Let w_l be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with lhs, 0
    Let w_r be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with rhs, 0
    Let w_o be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with result, 0
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than nw:
        Let a_l be proc bitset_word_addr with w_l, i
        Let a_r be proc bitset_word_addr with w_r, i
        Let a_o be proc bitset_word_addr with w_o, i
        Let v_l be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with a_l, 0
        Let v_r be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with a_r, 0
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with a_o, 0, v_l bitwise or v_r
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    Return result
End Process

@Reasoning
Allocate a new bitset holding the bitwise intersection of lhs and rhs.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Symmetric with bitset_union but uses AND.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(num_words). Allocates.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on num_bits mismatch or allocation failure.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "bitset_intersection" takes lhs as Integer, rhs as Integer returns Integer:
    If lhs is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If rhs is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let n_l be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with lhs, 8
    Let n_r be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with rhs, 8
    If n_l is not equal to n_r:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let result be proc bitset_create with n_l
    If result is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let nw be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with lhs, 16
    Let w_l be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with lhs, 0
    Let w_r be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with rhs, 0
    Let w_o be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with result, 0
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than nw:
        Let a_l be proc bitset_word_addr with w_l, i
        Let a_r be proc bitset_word_addr with w_r, i
        Let a_o be proc bitset_word_addr with w_o, i
        Let v_l be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with a_l, 0
        Let v_r be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with a_r, 0
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with a_o, 0, v_l bitwise and v_r
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    Return result
End Process

@Reasoning
Allocate a new bitset holding the bitwise difference lhs AND NOT rhs.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Allocates, then word-wise (lhs AND (NOT rhs)).
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(num_words). Allocates.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on num_bits mismatch or allocation failure.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "bitset_difference" takes lhs as Integer, rhs as Integer returns Integer:
    If lhs is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If rhs is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let n_l be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with lhs, 8
    Let n_r be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with rhs, 8
    If n_l is not equal to n_r:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let result be proc bitset_create with n_l
    If result is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let nw be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with lhs, 16
    Let w_l be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with lhs, 0
    Let w_r be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with rhs, 0
    Let w_o be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with result, 0
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than nw:
        Let a_l be proc bitset_word_addr with w_l, i
        Let a_r be proc bitset_word_addr with w_r, i
        Let a_o be proc bitset_word_addr with w_o, i
        Let v_l be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with a_l, 0
        Let v_r be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with a_r, 0
        Let not_r be v_r bitwise xor BITSET_FULL_WORD
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with a_o, 0, v_l bitwise and not_r
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    Return result
End Process

@Reasoning
Allocate a new bitset holding the symmetric difference lhs XOR rhs.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Allocates, word-wise XOR, then masks the tail.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(num_words). Allocates.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on num_bits mismatch or allocation failure.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "bitset_xor" takes lhs as Integer, rhs as Integer returns Integer:
    If lhs is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If rhs is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let n_l be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with lhs, 8
    Let n_r be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with rhs, 8
    If n_l is not equal to n_r:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let result be proc bitset_create with n_l
    If result is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let nw be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with lhs, 16
    Let w_l be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with lhs, 0
    Let w_r be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with rhs, 0
    Let w_o be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with result, 0
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than nw:
        Let a_l be proc bitset_word_addr with w_l, i
        Let a_r be proc bitset_word_addr with w_r, i
        Let a_o be proc bitset_word_addr with w_o, i
        Let v_l be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with a_l, 0
        Let v_r be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with a_r, 0
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with a_o, 0, v_l bitwise xor v_r
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    Let num_bits be n_l
    Let rem be num_bits modulo by BITSET_WORD_BITS
    If rem is not equal to 0:
        Let mask be proc bitset_tail_mask with num_bits
        Let last_addr be proc bitset_word_addr with w_o, nw minus 1
        Let cur be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with last_addr, 0
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with last_addr, 0, cur bitwise and mask
    End If
    Return result
End Process

@Reasoning
