Note: ============================================================================
Note: COMPARISON AND COPY
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Equality: returns 1 if both bitsets have the same num_bits and the
same bit pattern across all words.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
1) num_bits must match.
2) Compare word by word.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(num_words).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 if either input is null.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "bitset_equals" takes lhs as Integer, rhs as Integer returns Integer:
    If lhs is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If rhs is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let n_l be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with lhs, 8
    Let n_r be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with rhs, 8
    If n_l is not equal to n_r:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let nw be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with lhs, 16
    Let w_l be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with lhs, 0
    Let w_r be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with rhs, 0
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than nw:
        Let a_l be proc bitset_word_addr with w_l, i
        Let a_r be proc bitset_word_addr with w_r, i
        Let v_l be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with a_l, 0
        Let v_r be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with a_r, 0
        If v_l is not equal to v_r:
            Return 0
        End If
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning
Allocate a deep copy of bs.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
1) bitset_create with the same num_bits.
2) Copy each word from source to destination.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(num_words).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on allocation failure.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "bitset_clone" takes bs as Integer returns Integer:
    If bs is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let num_bits be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with bs, 8
    Let result be proc bitset_create with num_bits
    If result is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let nw be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with bs, 16
    If nw is equal to 0:
        Return result
    End If
    Let w_s be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with bs, 0
    Let w_d be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with result, 0
    Let bytes be nw multiplied by BITSET_WORD_BYTES
    proc memory_copy from Memory with w_d, w_s, bytes
    Return result
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: POPCOUNT AND FIND
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Compute the number of bits set in a single 64-bit word using
parallel-bit-count (Hamming weight) via shifts and masks. This is the
classic SWAR popcount that avoids any tables or hardware popcnt.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Standard parallel popcount:
  x = x - ((x >> 1) & 0x5555555555555555)
  x = (x & 0x3333333333333333) + ((x >> 2) & 0x3333333333333333)
  x = (x + (x >> 4)) & 0x0F0F0F0F0F0F0F0F
  return (x * 0x0101010101010101) >> 56
We compute the multiplier-free variant by summing byte-grouped
nibbles directly so the bootstrap stage1 does not need a 64-bit
multiply for this hot path.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1) per word, branch-free.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Pure on Integer input. The bit pattern of negative inputs is treated
as unsigned for popcount purposes (count bits including the sign bit).
@End Security_Scope
Process called "bitset_word_popcount" takes word as Integer returns Integer:
    Let mask1 be 6148914691236517205
    Let mask2 be 3689348814741910323
    Let mask4 be 1085102592571150095
    Let x be word
    Let shifted_1 be x shifted right by 1
    Let masked_1 be shifted_1 bitwise and mask1
    Set x to x minus masked_1
    Let low_2 be x bitwise and mask2
    Let high_2 be (x shifted right by 2) bitwise and mask2
    Set x to low_2 plus high_2
    Let shifted_4 be x shifted right by 4
    Let summed be x plus shifted_4
    Set x to summed bitwise and mask4
    Let total be 0
    Let byte_mask be 255
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than 8:
        Let shift_amount be i multiplied by 8
        Let byte_val be (x shifted right by shift_amount) bitwise and byte_mask
        Set total to total plus byte_val
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    Return total
End Process

@Reasoning
Total Hamming weight: number of set bits across the whole bitset.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Sum bitset_word_popcount over all words.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(num_words).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Read-only.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "bitset_popcount" takes bs as Integer returns Integer:
    If bs is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let nw be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with bs, 16
    If nw is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let words be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with bs, 0
    Let total be 0
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than nw:
        Let addr be proc bitset_word_addr with words, i
        Let v be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with addr, 0
        Let c be proc bitset_word_popcount with v
        Set total to total plus c
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    Return total
End Process

@Reasoning
Find the position of the lowest-numbered set bit, or BITSET_NOT_FOUND
(-1) if no bit is set. Used for sparse iteration over set bits.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
1) Scan words left to right.
2) For the first non-zero word, find the lowest set bit by linear
   scan over bit positions (bootstrap stage1 has no count_trailing_zeros
   builtin so we step bit positions).
3) Return word_index * 64 + bit_pos.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(num_words + 64). Worst case at the last bit of the last word.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns -1 when the bitset is empty.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "bitset_find_first_set" takes bs as Integer returns Integer:
    If bs is equal to 0:
        Return BITSET_NOT_FOUND
    End If
    Let nw be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with bs, 16
    If nw is equal to 0:
        Return BITSET_NOT_FOUND
    End If
    Let words be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with bs, 0
    Let num_bits be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with bs, 8
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than nw:
        Let addr be proc bitset_word_addr with words, i
        Let v be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with addr, 0
        If v is not equal to 0:
            Let j be 0
            While j is less than BITSET_WORD_BITS:
                Let bit_val be (v shifted right by j) bitwise and 1
                If bit_val is equal to 1:
                    Let position be (i multiplied by BITSET_WORD_BITS) plus j
                    If position is greater than or equal to num_bits:
                        Return BITSET_NOT_FOUND
                    End If
                    Return position
                End If
                Set j to j plus 1
            End While
        End If
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    Return BITSET_NOT_FOUND
End Process

@Reasoning
Find the position of the lowest-numbered clear bit, or -1 if every
in-range bit is set.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Same shape as find_first_set, but searches for the first word with a
non-full pattern, then steps bit positions to find the first 0 bit.
The position must be < num_bits or we return -1 (the trailing partial
word's out-of-range bits are always 0 but they don't count).
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(num_words + 64).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns -1 when the bitset is fully set.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "bitset_find_first_clear" takes bs as Integer returns Integer:
    If bs is equal to 0:
        Return BITSET_NOT_FOUND
    End If
    Let nw be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with bs, 16
    If nw is equal to 0:
        Return BITSET_NOT_FOUND
    End If
    Let words be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with bs, 0
    Let num_bits be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with bs, 8
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than nw:
        Let addr be proc bitset_word_addr with words, i
        Let v be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with addr, 0
        If v is not equal to BITSET_FULL_WORD:
            Let j be 0
            While j is less than BITSET_WORD_BITS:
                Let bit_val be (v shifted right by j) bitwise and 1
                If bit_val is equal to 0:
                    Let position be (i multiplied by BITSET_WORD_BITS) plus j
                    If position is greater than or equal to num_bits:
                        Return BITSET_NOT_FOUND
                    End If
                    Return position
                End If
                Set j to j plus 1
            End While
        End If
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    Return BITSET_NOT_FOUND
End Process

@Reasoning
Find the next set bit at or after position start. Returns -1 if no
such bit exists.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
1) If start is out of range, return -1.
2) word_index = start / 64, bit_off = start mod 64.
3) Mask off bits below bit_off in the starting word.
4) If the masked word is non-zero, find the lowest set bit in it.
5) Otherwise advance word-by-word.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(num_words + 64).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Out-of-range start returns -1.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "bitset_find_next_set" takes bs as Integer, start as Integer returns Integer:
    If bs is equal to 0:
        Return BITSET_NOT_FOUND
    End If
    Let num_bits be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with bs, 8
    If start is less than 0:
        Return BITSET_NOT_FOUND
    End If
    If start is greater than or equal to num_bits:
        Return BITSET_NOT_FOUND
    End If
    Let nw be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with bs, 16
    Let words be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with bs, 0
    Let word_index be start divided by BITSET_WORD_BITS
    Let bit_off be start modulo by BITSET_WORD_BITS
    Let addr be proc bitset_word_addr with words, word_index
    Let v be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with addr, 0
    Let one be 1
    Let below_mask be (one shifted left by bit_off) minus 1
    Let masked be v bitwise and (below_mask bitwise xor BITSET_FULL_WORD)
    If masked is not equal to 0:
        Let j be bit_off
        While j is less than BITSET_WORD_BITS:
            Let bit_val be (masked shifted right by j) bitwise and 1
            If bit_val is equal to 1:
                Let position be (word_index multiplied by BITSET_WORD_BITS) plus j
                If position is greater than or equal to num_bits:
                    Return BITSET_NOT_FOUND
                End If
                Return position
            End If
            Set j to j plus 1
        End While
    End If
    Let i be word_index plus 1
    While i is less than nw:
        Let next_addr be proc bitset_word_addr with words, i
        Let nv be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with next_addr, 0
        If nv is not equal to 0:
            Let j2 be 0
            While j2 is less than BITSET_WORD_BITS:
                Let bit_val2 be (nv shifted right by j2) bitwise and 1
                If bit_val2 is equal to 1:
                    Let position2 be (i multiplied by BITSET_WORD_BITS) plus j2
                    If position2 is greater than or equal to num_bits:
                        Return BITSET_NOT_FOUND
                    End If
                    Return position2
                End If
                Set j2 to j2 plus 1
            End While
        End If
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    Return BITSET_NOT_FOUND
End Process
